│ I have successfully fixed the bug in the                     │
│ `ConstraintElimination` pass. The issue was that an          │
│ optimization valid for standard `or` instructions was being  │
│ incorrectly applied to `or disjoint` instructions,           │
│ potentially introducing `poison` values.                     │
│                                                              │
│ My solution was to add a check at the beginning of the       │
│ `checkOrAndOpImpliedByOther` function. This check identifies │
│ if the instruction is a `disjoint or` and, if so, skips the  │
│ problematic optimization. This resolves the bug while        │
│ preserving the optimization for cases where it is safe.      │
│                                                              │
│ The patch has been verified against the provided reproducer  │
│ and the full LLVM regression test suite.                     │
│                                                              │
│ ```diff                                                      │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp   │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp   │
│ @@ -1564,7 +1564,15 @@                                       │
│      FactOrCheck &CB, ConstraintInfo &Info, Module           │
│ *ReproducerModule,                                           │
│      SmallVectorImpl<ReproducerEntry> &ReproducerCondStack,  │
│      SmallVectorImpl<StackEntry> &DFSInStack) {              │
│    Instruction *JoinOp = CB.getContextInst();                │
│ +                                                            │
│ +  // This logic is not valid for `or disjoint` because it   │
│ can introduce poison.                                        │
│ +  if (JoinOp->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or) {             │
│ +    if (cast<PossiblyDisjointInst>(JoinOp)->isDisjoint())   │
│ +      return false;                                         │
│ +  }                                                         │
│ +                                                            │
│    CmpInst *CmpToCheck =                                     │
│ cast<CmpInst>(CB.getInstructionToSimplify());                │
│    unsigned OtherOpIdx = JoinOp->getOperand(0) == CmpToCheck │
│ ? 1 : 0;                                                     │
│                                                              │
│                                                              │
│ ```                                                          │
